info.name: Feline
info.attribution:
The game layout, game design and game elements were done by GripenG and LawDawg and are released to the Public Domain by CC0. The tile patterns were made using https://pattern.monster/ under MIT License available at https://github.com/catchspider2002/svelte-svg-patterns. The cat head shape is in the public domain and is available at https://publicdomainvectors.org/en/free-clipart/Cat-face-line-art-vector-image/17125.html The following graphics are from Pixabay and are available under the Pixabay License: - Cat shape silhouettes: https://pixabay.com/vectors/animal-cat-clips-feline-kitten-1299486/ - Buttons: https://pixabay.com/vectors/buttons-fastners-assorted-buttons-312190/ and https://pixabay.com/vectors/colorful-prismatic-chromatic-1321413/ - Wood texture background: https://pixabay.com/photos/wood-boards-texture-wooden-brown-1846849/

Library image generated using the Midjourney artificial intelligence image generator, https://www.midjourney.com/home/, using the following prompt: "clowder of cats oil on canvas by lous wain --ar 1:1 --v 5.1"
info.description: Build a quilt using colorful hexagon tiles. Each player uses their own board. Gain points for matching patterns and colors. Most points wins.
info.helpText: Players take designated colored seats. Choose and place starting pieces then press Toggle Setup Button. Once play begins, players can switch to look at another player's board at any time using the colored buttons above the board. Scoring is automatic for the design goal tiles. Players must move cat and button tokens onto the board, which will also trigger an automatic score update.
